                            . Instead, we offer highly abstract representation of characters that are distinguished from one another only by colour, size, and human or non-human form, and optionally annotated with supplemental photographs of actors playing characters (see Figure 3.10; 
                                Roberts-Smith et al., Visualizing Theatre Historiography

